## Install VirtualBox and Windows Server 2022

- Install VirtualBox on computer
- Download Microsoft Windows Server 2022 ISO
- Create VM in VirtualBox
  - `new > (name it CA-DC-01) > select windows server 2022 > finish`
  - `right click VM > settings > configure CPU, memory, etc. > finish`
  - `settings > network`
    - `adapter 1 > internal network > LABNET`
    - `adapter 2 > NAT`
  - `start VM > select downloaded ISO file`

---

## Configure CA-DC-01 Static IP

- On server:
  - `Windows + R > ncpa.cpl`
  - `right click internal adapter > properties`
  - `internet protocol version 4 (TCP/IPv4)`

- Configure:
  - `IP Address: 192.168.10.10`
  - `Subnet Mask: 255.255.255.0`
  - `Default Gateway: leave blank`
  - `Preferred DNS: 192.168.10.10`

---

## Install Active Directory on Server

- Rename server:
  - `this pc > properties > rename this pc`
  - `rename to: CA-DC-01`

- Install AD:
  - `server manager > manage > add roles and features`
  - `select active directory domain services`
  - `install`
  - `promote this server to a domain controller`
  - `add a new forest`
  - `create domain name`
  - `complete installation and restart`

---

## Install Guest Additions and Shared Folder

- On VirtualBox:
  - `devices > insert guest additions CD image`

- Set up shared folder:
  - `devices > shared folders`

- On server VM:
  - `open file explorer`
  - `eject VirtualBox drive`
  - `shared folder now accessible between host and VM`

